			<ns0:name>b...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/105821748722532785568/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">this is the NaCl half of the issue.

Currently, the NaCl browser plugin only detects nexe crashes when it tries to communicate with it.  This makes various in-browser crash tests flaky, since if the startup handshake has completed by the time the nexe crashes, the plugin won't need to communicate with the test any more, and the crashed nexe / service runtime would go undetected -- and the test will time out (currently, 20s inactivity) before failing.

The reverse channel service thread detects nexe crashes immediately, but currently does not generate the crash progress event.  It should.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2011-09-20T21:50:29.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2011-09-09T04:47:00.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:status>Fixed</ns2:status><ns2:owner>
